article.headline: Wagner 18, Sacred Heart 15
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Jason Butler rushed for a career-high 157 yards, Piotr Czech kicked three field goals and Wagner beat Sacred Heart 18-15 on Saturday in a Northeast Conference game. Czech broke a 15-all tie with under eight minutes with a 47-yard field goal. He also was successful from 46 and 31 yards for the Seahawks (3-1, 1-0). Butler rushed 37 times for his fourth straight 100-yard game. Tyler McKeon completed 20 of 34 passes for 207 yards with an interception for the Pioneers (2-3, 0-1). Steve Tedesco caught 11 passes for 143 yards, both career highs. Sacred Heart, down 12-0 early in the third quarter, tied the score at 15 with just more than 12 minutes remaining on Jason Payne's 25-yard run.
